{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01U5ZaVqNW1qxPv5CdWvwn6W","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me compile the comprehensive inventory report.\n\n## Frontend Platform App Inventory Report\n\n### 1. Wallet Provider Wrapping (`src/main.tsx`)\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/main.tsx`\n\n- **Lines 1-21**: Full implementation\n- **Line 3**: Imports `WalletProvider` from `@rng-utopia/wallet`\n- **Lines 11-12**: Comment explaining delegation to MockWalletProvider or RealWalletProvider based on `VITE_MOCK_MODE`\n- **Lines 13-20**: App wrapped with `<ErrorBoundary>` → `<WalletProvider>` → `<App />`\n\n**Key Finding**: WalletProvider automatically selects mock or real mode based on environment variable.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Wallet UI Integration (`src/App.tsx`)\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/App.tsx`\n\n**Line 13**: Imports wallet hooks\n```typescript\nimport { useWallet, useBalance } from \"@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks\";\n```\n\n**Lines 269-270**: Hook usage in AppContent\n```typescript\nconst { connected, connecting, address, connect, disconnect } = useWallet();\nconst { formatted } = useBalance();\n```\n\n**Lines 414-422**: Wallet icon rendering (bottom-right scene area)\n```typescript\n<div\n  className={`rpg-wallet-icon ${connected ? \"rpg-wallet-icon--connected\" : \"\"} ${connecting ? \"rpg-wallet-icon--connecting\" : \"\"}`}\n  onClick={() => connected ? disconnect() : connect()}\n  title={connected ? `$${formatted ?? \"0\"}` : \"Connect Wallet\"}\n>\n  <span className=\"rpg-wallet-icon__amount\">\n    {connecting ? \"...\" : connected ? `$${formatted ?? \"0\"}` : \"—\"}\n  </span>\n  <div className=\"rpg-wallet-icon__bag\" />\n</div>\n```\n\n**States Displayed**:\n- **Disconnected**: Shows \"—\" (em dash), no connected class\n- **Connecting**: Shows \"...\", has connecting class\n- **Connected**: Shows formatted balance (e.g., \"$1.23\"), has connected class\n\n---\n\n### 3. Coinflip Context - Wallet Integration\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx`\n\n#### Hook Usage (Lines 21, 97-98)\n```typescript\nimport { useWallet, useConnection } from \"@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks\";\n// ...\nconst { connected, publicKey, sendTransaction } = useWallet();\nconst { connection } = useConnection();\n```\n\n#### parseTransactionError Function (Lines 23-62)\n**Comprehensive error mapping**:\n\n- **Line 28-30**: `\"Wallet not connected\"` / `\"WalletNotConnectedError\"`\n- **Line 33-35**: `\"User rejected\"` / `\"Transaction cancelled\"`\n- **Line 38-40**: `\"insufficient lamports\"` / `\"Insufficient funds\"` / `\"0x1\"` → Insufficient balance\n- **Line 43-45**: `\"already in use\"` → You already have an active match\n- **Line 48-50**: `\"Failed to fetch\"` / `\"NetworkError\"` / `\"ECONNREFUSED\"` → Network error\n- **Line 53-58**: Anchor program errors:\n  - `\"InvalidPhase\"` → Match no longer available\n  - `\"CannotJoinOwnMatch\"` → Cannot join own match\n- **Line 61**: Generic fallback with truncation at 100 chars\n\n#### sendTransaction Calls\n\n1. **createMatch** (Line 186)\n   ```typescript\n   await sendTransaction(transaction);\n   ```\n   - Error handling: Line 197 `setError(parseTransactionError(err))`\n   - Wrapped in try/finally with `setCreating(true/false)`\n\n2. **joinMatch** (Line 229)\n   ```typescript\n   await sendTransaction(transaction);\n   ```\n   - Error handling: Line 239 `setError(parseTransactionError(err))`\n   - Wrapped in try/finally with `setJoining(true/false)` and `setJoiningMatchId(matchId/null)`\n\n3. **cancelMatch** (Line 257)\n   ```typescript\n   await sendTransaction(transaction);\n   ```\n   - Error handling: Line 261 `setError(parseTransactionError(err))`\n\n4. **claimPayout** (Line 286)\n   ```typescript\n   await sendTransaction(transaction);\n   ```\n   - Error handling: Line 291 `setError(parseTransactionError(err))`\n   - Wrapped in try/finally with `setClaiming(true/false)`\n\n---\n\n### 4. Transaction Builders (`src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts`)\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts`\n\n#### Constants (Lines 22-36)\n- **Line 22-25**: `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` from env or IDL\n- **Lines 28-30**: MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF constants (queue, program ID, identity)\n- **Lines 33-35**: On-chain phase constants\n\n#### Transaction Builders\n\n1. **buildCreateMatchTx** (Lines 222-248)\n   - Returns: `{ transaction: Transaction; matchPda: PublicKey }`\n   - Sets `tx.feePayer = creator`\n   - Fetches recent blockhash\n\n2. **buildJoinMatchTx** (Lines 250-278)\n   - Takes opponent and matchCreator\n   - Includes VRF accounts (config, oracleQueue, programIdentity, vrfProgram, slotHashes)\n   - Returns Transaction with feePayer set\n\n3. **buildCancelMatchTx** (Lines 280-301)\n   - Simple cancel instruction\n   - Returns Transaction\n\n4. **buildClaimPayoutTx** (Lines 303-351)\n   - Fetches config to get treasury address (Line 314)\n   - Derives player profile PDAs for CPI (Lines 322-329)\n   - Includes all required accounts for platform CPI\n   - Returns Transaction\n\n**Key Finding**: All transactions are pre-built with proper accounts, blockhash, and feePayer before being passed to `sendTransaction`.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Environment Configuration\n\n#### `.env.example` (Lines 1-7)\n```bash\nVITE_MOCK_MODE=true\nVITE_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com\nVITE_SOLANA_NETWORK=devnet\n```\n\n#### `.env.devnet` (Lines 1-7)\n```bash\nVITE_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com\nVITE_SOLANA_NETWORK=devnet\nVITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID=H8Q2R1bUxzfUkV6WRRiZxYWwGfCr794AcnskWpsRQJf3\nVITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID=dYJcBccf1M7yDePcgmiytiEtwr7n4fAaLQAhVPNHgVM\n```\n\n**Note**: `.env.example` shows `VITE_MOCK_MODE=true` (default for development). Real mode sets `VITE_MO