<Uint8Array> => {\n      if (!connected) {\n        throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected\");\n      }\n      // Return a deterministic signature from the keypair's secret key\n      const sig = new Uint8Array(64);\n      sig.set(keypair.secretKey.slice(0, 64));\n      return sig;\n    },\n    [connected, keypair],\n  );\n","numLines":30,"startLine":55,"totalLines":119}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VtA62q7KQfkRp6VHw7rFQL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. I now have all the evidence I need. Let me check one more thing — whether there's an explicit `confirmTransaction` in the `RealWalletProvider` `sendTransaction` path. From the code at `RealWalletProvider.tsx:51`, `adapter.sendTransaction(transaction, connection)` delegates to the wallet adapter which returns the signature but doesn't await confirmation. The `CoinflipContext` doesn't call `confirmTransaction` either — it just does `await sendTransaction(transaction)` then immediately fetches the match. This is a gap for FR-3 criterion about \"Transaction confirmation is awaited before updating UI state.\"\n\nLet me also check the `useBalance` return shape vs spec requirements.\n\nNow I have everything. Let me write the gap analysis report."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1328,"cache_read_input_tokens":75398,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1328},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0f6af63c-d689-426d-9dd8-218925b8488a","uuid":"ccaee3b0-ad5f-4963-8084-82fa0e8fd2fa"}
